The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 17: The government has released an additional six lakh tonnes of sugar for the April-June quarter. Sugar prices in many places fell Rs 15-60 a quintal following the Centres decision. We expect that there will be absolutely no shortage of sugar in the market, the government said today. The additional release will bring the total sugar available for free sale in the market to 60 lakh tonnes during the quarter.                            
	 New Delhi, April 17: The Prime Ministers economic advisory council expects the countrys economy to grow at over seven per cent in the current fiscal as it has already started showing signs of recovery. Seven per cent plus is what my 2009-10 overall forecast is, council chairman Suresh Tendulkar said.                            
	 New Delhi, April 17: The RBI has informed banks that loans against intangible collaterals such as rights and licences should not be counted as secured and such advances should be disclosed.                            
	 New Delhi, April 17: Sebi will carry out a probe to find out whether there was any violation of takeover norms in Neeraj Singhal-led Bhushan Groups stake purchase in Orissa Sponge.                             
	 Mumbai, April 17: Pfizers $36-million (Rs 680 crore) open offer to the shareholders of its Indian arm will begin on June 10 and close on June 29. Pfizer Investments Netherlands will make a tender offer to acquire a further 33.77 per cent stake in Pfizer Ltd at Rs 675 per share.                            
	 New Delhi, April 17: The civil aviation ministry has cleared the proposal for mandatory quoting of all-inclusive fares by the Indian airlines, to remove ambiguity in the air fare structure.                            
